Phase 2 Authentication — Complete

Authentication Architecture

The frontend uses an in-memory access token + httpOnly refresh cookie pattern:
- accessToken lives only in Zustand store (never localStorage/sessionStorage)
- Refresh token is an httpOnly cookie — JavaScript cannot read it
- On app startup, SessionProvider calls tryRefresh() to silently restore sessions
- On 401, apiClient interceptor queues all in-flight requests, calls /auth/refresh, replays them

