---
Fix Verification

#1 — Route protection
The authoring sub-tree uses a pathless layout route with RoleGate roles={['content_manager', 'platform_admin']}. Any other authenticated role navigating to /content/rooms/create, /content/courses/create, /content/problems/create, or /content/rooms/:slug/edit is redirected to /unauthorized. The catalog read-only routes remain open to all authenticated users.

#2 — Edit workflow
RoomEditPage loads room data via useRoom(slug), populates the form via useEffect with form.reset(), uses the shared BlockEditor (with wrapAllWithKeys to give existing blocks stable keys), and saves via useUpdateRoom({ id, dto }). The "Edit" button in RoomDetailPage now resolves to a registered route. Non-draft rooms show a status guard screen rather than allowing edits.

#3 — Search debounce
All four search inputs debounce at 350ms using the useDebounce hook. The raw search/query state updates immediately (for the input display), while the debounced value is what drives the query key. Zero API calls fire while the user is mid-keystroke.

#4 — Stable React keys
BlockEditor defines EditorBlock = ContentBlock & { _editorKey: string }. Keys are generated with crypto.randomUUID() at block creation time and are preserved through any number of updates, additions, and removals. React reconciles by key, not index. stripEditorKeys() removes _editorKey before the payload goes to the API. The type is local to BlockEditor.tsx — ContentBlock in content.types.ts is unchanged.

#5 — No empty-string IDs in mutation closures
All three hooks changed: useRoomLifecycle mutations receive { id, slug } as the mutation variable; usePublishProblem receives { problemId, slug }; useRemoveRoomFromCourse receives { courseId, roomId }. The hooks no longer close over any ID — there is no constructor parameter to pass an empty string to. Malformed URLs like /rooms//approve are now impossible.

#6 — Orphaned problem creation
onSubmit is split into two phases with a hard return between them. If createProblem fails, the user sees "Failed to create problem. Nothing was saved." and stays on the form. If createProblem succeeds but some addTestCase calls fail, the user is navigated to the newly-created problem detail page with a toast.warning listing which test case numbers failed and the problem ID — ensuring they can never believe nothing was created when a draft problem actually exists.

