Backend Limitations Documented

1. Certificate Generator Produces HTML, Not PDF

Audit finding: cert generator saves HTML not PDF (uses S3 not Puppeteer despite Dockerfile having Chromium)
Impact: The download endpoint returns HTML-backed content even with a .pdf filename.
UI treatment: CertificateDetailPage shows an amber notice. CertificateDownloadButton names the file .pdf but backend content may be HTML. Admin page shows this in the limitations notice.

2. Reissue Does Not Revoke Old Certificate

Audit finding: reissueCertificate does not revoke old cert
Impact: Calling /certificates/:id/reissue creates a new certificate generation job but the old issued record remains valid. Multiple active versions may temporarily coexist.
UI treatment: Admin page shows warning. Frontend renders backend state as-is; no frontend workaround attempted.

3. Tenant Ownership Check Insufficient

Audit finding: tenant ownership check insufficient (line 186-188)
Impact: Admin revoke/reissue may allow cross-tenant operations.
UI treatment: Frontend renders backend responses as provided; no tenant filtering added.

